  <title translate="true">CSUB Example: Head Observations</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">CSUB Example: Head Observations</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The model has head observations at the locations of the wells and all the layers above and below them. We can&apos;t use the same objects that we used to define the wells because that wouldn&apos;t make the cells above and below the wells observation locations.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The first step is to check the check box for the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="OBS_Observation_Utility_Packag" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW 6 Observation Utility</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Packages_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. For this example, we will use a text format and set the number of digits to 10. Then click OK to close the dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="CSubExampleActivateObsUtil.png" scale="60.00%" width="470" height="353" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Activating the MODFLOW 6 Observation Utility</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Next, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Points" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">create a point object</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> on the top view of the model at the location of one of the wells. Make sure the Z-coordinates of the object go through all the layers.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="CSubExampleHeadObsBasic.png" scale="60.00%" width="472" height="352" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Specifying Elevations for Head Observation</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">On the MODFLOW Features tab, specify that the object will define a head observation and specify a name for the observations.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="CSubExampleHeadObsSelect.png" scale="60.00%" width="472" height="352" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Specifying Head Observations</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">After clicking OK to close the dialog box, add a new section to the object at the location of the other well using the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Add point sections</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> </text><image src="AddPoints.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Add Point Sections button</title></image><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> button</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
